<div class="container">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div id="comments-4">
        
            <article id="comment-825">
              <time datetime="2011-06-07">June 07, 2011</time>
              <p>Whenever I am in London...Fantastic food, amazing atmosphere. I love it.</p>
              <p class="author">From Ondrej</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-821">
              <time datetime="2011-06-06">June 06, 2011</time>
              <p>On a trip to London at the weekend to celebrate my birthday, we went to the restaurant round the corner from our hotel in Shoreditch. I was a little sceptical having never eaten thai but the staff were very helpful, giving menu suggestions and the food was amazing. I stayed safe with a chicken dish which was very nice but tried other dishes of beef and even ostrich which was sensational! We will definitely be dining there again on our next visit and will recommend to others. :)</p>
              <p class="author">From Holly</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-809">
              <time datetime="2011-05-30">May 30, 2011</time>
              <p>Fantastic food....My fav restaurant in London.....Ull should open up in Mumbai, India...</p>
              <p class="author">From Sheekha Khan</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-794">
              <time datetime="2011-05-04">May 04, 2011</time>
              <p>Absolutely fantastic food! Every time I am in London We usually end up choosing here to eat. The pandan chicken is amazing- Love the sauce that comes with it. The green chicken curry and sticky rice is second to none. Great staff and lovely decor. See you soon!</p>
              <p class="author">From Pauline sharma</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-790">
              <time datetime="2011-05-04">May 04, 2011</time>
              <p>Busaba is a regular meeting point for my boyfriend and I. Food is absolutely stunning and I've never left feeling hungry. PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE bring back the Geng Gari Gai! Greatest thing ever!</p>
              <p class="author">From Asha</p>
    
            </article>

